140:{"id": "ASM-0532", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "g3-llmproxy estimand gap: HS3 is a claim about human ordinary usage; LLM pass-A truth-of-claim and pass-B literal condition-satisfaction judgments approximate human judgments with unproven systematic offsets (the literalism channel can push the necessity-violation rate up via hyper-literal condition failures or down via charitable reading); neither proxy verdict direction measures the human rates.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g3-llmproxy.json extrapolation_envelope_verbatim clause 1", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Run the frozen human g3 (two independent annotators) on the identical 200 instances; per-item human-vs-proxy deltas on q1/q2 measure the offset and its direction directly."}
141:{"id": "ASM-0533", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "g3-llmproxy escape + coverage gates: cannot-say is neither violation nor satisfaction (the pinned protocol's stated treatment); per judge per pass, cannot-say > 5% or no-label > 5% => INSTRUMENT-INVALID (the protocol's ~5% re-examination line made mechanical, fail-closed); an instance is decisive for a judge iff q1 and q2 are both in {yes,no}; n_dual_decisive >= 170 of 200 keeps both Wilson branches reachable (PASS-analog up to ~11 union violations, FAIL-analog from ~24 concordant, at the floor).", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g3-llmproxy.json; data/instance-descriptions/annotation-protocol.md (open run-stage decision 3)", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "The human protocol proposed but did not freeze the cannot-say treatment; the proxy must fix it mechanically pre-run, and adopting the protocol's own proposal at its own ~5% line is the minimal-choice instantiation."}
142:{"id": "ASM-0534", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "g3-llmproxy probe-B construction: 30 seed-pinned instances are presented in pass-B form with the condition set of a DIFFERENT concept (concept-level Sattolo cycle over the 20 condition_set_ids), original text + bindings verbatim; 'no' is the correct answer by construction (another concept's conditions, roles largely unbound); only q2=yes counts as false satisfaction (cannot-say is non-endorsement); false-satisfaction >= 0.30 or probe coverage < 27/30 invalidates that judge's instrument; probes never enter counts.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g3-llmproxy.json; poc/g3-llmproxy/design.md S5", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "The direct pass-B analog of the house content-scramble control: it bounds the yes-saying channel that would fabricate a low violation rate, is constructible from pinned materials without gold labels, and unbound-role artifacts are handled by counting only affirmative endorsement as failure."}
148:{"id": "ASM-0550", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "llmproxy stand-in policy (shared, binding on g9-llmproxy, g3-llmproxy, m0a-llmproxy): per maintainer request (2026-07-10), blind kernel-instance-naive LLM judges stand in for the outstanding human annotation/review passes so the experiments run now and are human-verified later, exactly on the f2b-transfer-llmproxy model. Every proxy record: (a) takes a FRESH id and leaves the human record/pre-registration byte-untouched as the sole gold-standard adjudicator; (b) envelopes its verdict as a WEAK FEASIBILITY PROXY that substitutes for no part of the human pass, is quarantined and uncitable-as-final, and licenses ONLY programme sequencing / continued investment, never a claim upgrade; (c) never fills the human record's pins, never consumes its annotation round, and never triggers the human record's DAG consequences.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/f2b-transfer-llmproxy.json (frozen precedent) + registry/experiments/g9-llmproxy.json, g3-llmproxy.json, m0a-llmproxy.json", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "The f2b-transfer-llmproxy precedent (frozen, run, PASS, audit-confirmed, Fable-assessed) established that a fully-enveloped LLM stand-in yields real sequencing value (cheap-kill exposure, comparator pinning, operational de-risking) at near-zero cost without contaminating the human gold standard; this ASM fixes that discipline as the shared policy for the three new proxies. It falls away experiment-by-experiment as each human pass runs."}
150:{"id": "ASM-0552", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "llmproxy tradition-familiarity direction (shared; generalises ASM-0021 beyond the f2b line): NSM literature, NSM-style explications and reductive-paraphrase conventions are plausibly in BOTH judge vendors' training data, so proxy judges may endorse familiar STYLE rather than judge content; this plausibly inflates endorsement-type statistics (g9 composite, m0a 'correct' rates) and has unproven direction on g3's violation rates; the deranged probes bound only the crudest form in each record.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g9-llmproxy.json, g3-llmproxy.json, m0a-llmproxy.json extrapolation envelopes; ASM-0021", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Each human pass on identical items (g9.review sheets, g3 instances, m0a annotation sample) measures the human-vs-proxy delta directly; jointly with the f2b human round these give the familiarity channel's sign and size across four task types."}
151:{"id": "ASM-0553", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "llmproxy comparator + non-contamination discipline (shared): every proxy pins its per-item labels so the eventual human pass yields a free per-item human-vs-proxy bias measurement; conversely, proxy outputs (labels, run logs, derived rates, verdicts) must NEVER be shown to a future human annotator/reviewer for the same items before their sheets are submitted, and proxy runs write NOTHING under the pinned human-materials trees (data/authored-explication-set/, data/instance-descriptions/, mapper/m0/ inputs); a violation contaminates the human gold standard and is a boundary-stop incident, escalate to the maintainer.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g9-llmproxy.json, g3-llmproxy.json, m0a-llmproxy.json (stage_discipline + BINDING-NOTE assumptions)", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "The comparator role is the proxies' most durable scientific value (the f2b assessment's finding), and it survives only if the human passes stay naive; making the quarantine an explicit registered obligation binds every future runner and coordinator, not just this design."}
183:{"id": "ASM-0650", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "g3-llmproxy-v2 pass-B output-handling robustness fix (the ONLY delta from the superseded frozen g3-llmproxy, frozen_sha256 a50710609fe41d2b2b185400f95ee31594ef49f5575b331c1976f923b531c2b8, whose run ABORTED 2026-07-10 on the section-7 >10-no-label gate: judge-pB, claude-haiku-4-5 headless, systematically wrapped its two-field pass-B answer object in a ```json markdown code fence on 24/26 attempted real pass-B items while the pinned section-5 contract accepted only a bare JSON object; judge-pA server-side output schema unaffected, pass-A 200/200 labelled for both judges; the model's own preflight calibration answers were unfenced, so a model-side calibration item cannot exercise the defect): (1) the judge-pB pass-B format-only system prompt (poc/g3-llmproxy-v2/judge-pB-system-prompt-pass-b.txt) now explicitly requires a bare raw {...} object starting with { and ending with } - no markdown code fence, no ``` characters, no language tag, no prose; (2) the section-5 extraction contract gains a uniform content-blind FENCE NORMALIZATION applied to the raw answer string of both judges, all passes and probes, BEFORE json parsing: strip ASCII whitespace, and iff the string both starts and ends with ``` remove exactly one fence layer (opening ``` + optional [A-Za-z0-9_-]{0,16} language tag + optional spaces/tabs + the first newline when present, and the closing ```), re-strip, single layer only, then json.loads over the entire remaining string to exactly one JSON object; the reference implementation is extract_answer_object/normalize_token in the pinned analysis/g3_llmproxy_v2.py and the runner MUST label through it (a reimplementation is a spec violation); (3) preflight adds the runner-local fenced-extraction self-check cal:g3lp-x1 (python3 analysis/g3_llmproxy_v2.py --selftest, whose pinned fixtures include the aborted run's exact fenced pass-B bytes) as a precondition of both judges' preflight_pass, before any judge call. Fence normalization is FORMAT normalization in the same class as the existing whitespace/trailing-period token normalization: deterministic, evaluated before any answer field is read, unable to change which label is extracted - never answer repair; first-valid-answer-final and the <=3-content-attempt/no-label accounting are unchanged. The estimand, design, brackets, gates, verdict rules, budget and blinding are byte-carried from the superseded record; this is an extraction-contract robustness change only and does not affect the estimand.", "backing_ref": "poc/g3-llmproxy/opus-runs/20260710T194903Z/judge-pB-haiku45/run-log.txt (parse_fail captures); registry/experiments/g3-llmproxy-v2.json; poc/g3-llmproxy-v2/judge-invocation.md sections 5/8; analysis/g3_llmproxy_v2.py (extraction fixtures)", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "The fenced answers were systematic and content-complete - the object inside the fence was well-formed with plausible labels - so rejecting them measures CLI output-formatting behaviour, not the annotation instrument the record exists to measure. Belt-and-suspenders (the prompt forbids the fence AND the extraction tolerates one layer if the model adds it anyway) makes pass-B robust in both directions without touching what is measured, and the runner-local fixture check proves the tolerance before any spend, which the v1 model-side calibration provably could not."}
184:{"id": "ASM-0651", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "g3-llmproxy-v2 supersession + custody mechanics: (1) g3-llmproxy-v2 SUPERSEDES g3-llmproxy via the record's supersedes field; the v1 record stays FROZEN as immutable history (frozen-index entry untouched), is never run, and its PINNED-AT-INPUTS g3-annot-llmproxy corpus placeholder is deliberately left unfilled - no ops amendment may ever complete it; (2) v2 outputs land in the DISJOINT corpus data/g3-annot-llmproxy-v2/ (filled by ops amendment on the v2 record) and provenance in poc/g3-llmproxy-v2/opus-runs/, so no byte the v1 record pinned is ever mutated and no v2 output byte is attributable to v1; the v2 run writes NOTHING under poc/g3-llmproxy/ or data/g3-annot-llmproxy/; (3) unchanged artifacts are carried by their existing v1 paths + sha256 pins (poc/g3-llmproxy/ templates, schemas, pass-A system prompt, probe set + manifest + builder, calibration items; data/instance-descriptions/; analysis/g3.py reference) - shared pinned bytes, retained read-only; only the pass-B system prompt, the judge-invocation spec, the analysis script and the prereg doc carry fresh v2 paths + pins; (4) all governing stipulations of the superseded record carry over verbatim (ASM-0530-0534, ASM-0550-0554, ASM-0642, and ASM-0644 including the mandatory per-call init.tools==[] hard gate with zero tool_use blocks, permission_denials==[] and num_turns==1); the v2 spec is staged 2026-07-10, so ASM-0644's after-2026-07-10 --strict-mcp-config clause is not triggered and the judge invocation bytes stay identical to v1; (5) the aborted v1 run's provenance (poc/g3-llmproxy/opus-runs/20260710T194903Z/) is retained read-only as the defect evidence; its labels and captures are QUARANTINED - nothing is reused (no reused_from; the v1 run logged no results-log rows) and v2 re-runs both judges' both passes in full from preflight.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g3-llmproxy-v2.json (supersedes field); registry/experiments/g3-llmproxy.json frozen_sha256 a50710609fe41d2b2b185400f95ee31594ef49f5575b331c1976f923b531c2b8; registry/frozen-index.json; poc/g3-llmproxy-v2/judge-invocation.md sections 0/9", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "Frozen records are immutable (P2 section 1.1): a defect in a frozen-but-unrunnable harness is corrected by a fresh superseding id that re-pins only the changed bytes, keeps every unchanged byte at its already-pinned path, and keeps output trees disjoint so provenance attribution stays unambiguous between the aborted v1 evidence and the v2 re-run."}
193:{"id": "ASM-0740", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "g3-llmproxy-v3 section-6 blinding-scan scope amendment (the ratified truthstyle-2x2 Amendment-A1 rule, ASM-0660, reused in its exact form): on the two HARNESS-CAPTURED surfaces events.jsonl and stderr.log - NEVER on user-prompt.txt - a case-insensitive blind-token match (kernel/nsm/necessity/sufficiency/hypothesis) is excluded from being a HIT iff, in the original pre-lowercase bytes, it lies wholly inside the base62 TAIL of a maximal Anthropic-format vendor identifier literal (req|msg)_[0-9A-Za-z]{20,48} with lowercase-exact prefix and non-word-adjacent boundaries (runs longer than 48 fail maximality - fail-closed); uniform over all five tokens; every byte outside qualifying tails scans byte-identically to the superseded v2 contract; ADDITIONALLY the section-5 RAW answer string (judge-emitted bytes) is re-scanned with ZERO exclusions (answer-surface strictness), so a real leak in item bytes or judge-emitted answer text still ABORTS. Reference implementation blinding_scan/_vendor_id_tail_spans/answer_blinding_hit in the pinned analysis/g3_llmproxy_v3.py (adapted from the A1 section-9.5 normative code; no g3 token is hex-embeddable, so the truthstyle hex-run branch has no analogue); the runner imports it, never reimplements; the section-8 preflight selftest proves the EXACT v2-abort bytes excluded and real-leak shapes still aborting. Motivation (measured): the v2 run 20260710T204828Z aborted on pass-A item g3-friend-07 when the pinned v2 whole-file grep hit nsM inside the harness-stamped request_id req_011Ccu3G1KQZ8ciX3SvEfnsM at events.jsonl offset 2242 - user-prompt clean, stderr empty, answer clean, judge never saw the token; every captured judge-pB attempt carries exactly two such 24-char-tail ids (judge-pA/codex: zero), so a perfectly blind 430-call judge-pB run expects ~0.6 coincidental nsm hits and the unamended scan aborts a clean run with probability ~0.5 under the null - a control firing on vendor machinery under the null detects nothing.", "backing_ref": "registry/corrections/truthstyle-2x2/4-blinding-audit-amendment-a1.json (ratified A1 rule, ASM-0660); poc/truthstyle-2x2/blinding-audit-clarification.md section 9; poc/g3-llmproxy-v2/opus-runs/20260710T204828Z/judge-pB-haiku45/run-log.txt and passA/g3-friend-07/c1_t0/events.jsonl (the measured false positive); analysis/g3_llmproxy_v3.py --selftest (fixtures incl. the verbatim abort-byte slice)", "rationale": "Base62 vendor-id tails can spell any pinned token by arithmetic coincidence (the A1 section-9.2 argument, byte-for-byte the same channel: two ids per captured judge-pB call, 22 windows x (2/62)^3 per id), so the unamended predicate fires with ~coin-flip probability per clean run and has no discriminative power on this channel; the exclusion is format-anchored, maximality-checked, fail-closed and surface-restricted, so item contamination and judge echoes fire byte-identically to v2, and the added zero-exclusion answer-surface scan closes the residual-risk shape A1 section-9.6 could only disclose, at zero false-positive cost (the valid answer grammar contains no base62 ids). Amending the scan scope preserves the control; scrubbing provenance or dropping surfaces would not.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "any v3-scan hit at run time is a boundary stop back to Fable (never a runner improvisation); any future vendor id format outside the (req|msg)_ 20-48-base62 shape that coincidentally spells a token will abort again and is its own boundary stop"}
194:{"id": "ASM-0741", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "g3-llmproxy-v3 custody + supersession: v3 supersedes g3-llmproxy-v2 (frozen_sha256 5c8002b3b52d0641b28ca4aee7ab243a78cca40f111264a043253da1f33cb885) after its section-6 blinding FALSE-POSITIVE abort; the fix is blinding-scan-scope ONLY (ASM-0740), carried on TOP of v2's fence fix - the v2 fence-hardened pass-B system prompt is carried byte-identical at its v2 path+pin (poc/g3-llmproxy-v2/judge-pB-system-prompt-pass-b.txt, d0672138...), the section-5 fence-normalization extraction (ASM-0650) and all v2 design/estimand/bracket/gate/verdict/budget bytes carry forward verbatim; only the judge-invocation spec, the analysis script and the prereg doc get fresh v3 paths+pins; outputs land in the DISJOINT corpus data/g3-annot-llmproxy-v3 and provenance in poc/g3-llmproxy-v3/opus-runs; the superseded records' g3-annot-llmproxy and g3-annot-llmproxy-v2 placeholders stay unfilled forever; NOTHING from the aborted v2 run is reused (full re-run, both judges, both passes, from preflight); the aborted run's provenance is retained byte-verbatim read-only as defect evidence and the g3-friend-07 request_id bytes are NOT scrubbed (under ASM-0740 they are a listed, auditor-inspectable vendor-id exclusion; the v3-form sweep over all 131 retained v2 attempts is GREEN: strict scan exactly the one g3-friend-07 hit, amended scan zero hits). Disclosure (no selection effect): no v2 label file was ever assembled or written (responses are written only at pass END and no pass ended); the runner log displayed per-item q1 fields for the ~40 processed pass-A items and the coordinator read the abort context (one request_id literal) during diagnosis; those void partials are discarded and enter no statistic; the re-run criterion (detector false positive on machinery metadata) is structural, not outcome-dependent; first-valid-answer-final bars outcome-conditioned re-rolls.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g3-llmproxy-v2.json (frozen, immutable); poc/g3-llmproxy-v2/opus-runs/20260710T204828Z/ (retained provenance, 131 attempt captures); registry/corrections/truthstyle-2x2/4-blinding-audit-amendment-a1.json (the A1 no-scrub + re-derivability precedent, section 9.7 shape)", "rationale": "Frozen records are immutable, so a defect in a pinned control is a fresh superseding id (the ASM-0650/0651 v1-to-v2 precedent applied a second time); retaining the aborted bytes unscrubbed preserves auditor re-derivability - the strict v2-form scan, and the amended v3-form scan can each be independently re-run over the SAME retained bytes and must disagree in exactly the one measured place; a disjoint output corpus keeps the superseded placeholders unfilled and the eventual human round uncontaminated.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "discharged when the g3-llmproxy-v3 record freezes with these custody bytes and the v3 run completes (or the record is itself superseded)"}
196:{"id": "ASM-0761", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "In-flight-item non-deferral ruling (Fable, 2026-07-11): the capstone synthesis is authored as the DEFINITIVE STANDING verdict now, not deferred for any in-flight item. The two in-flight items are (i) g3-llmproxy-v3 (DRAFT proxy re-run, blinding-scan fix) which is a WEAK proxy that by construction can neither fire nor discharge the frozen g3's own necessity kill, hence refine-only; and (ii) the knull plain-arm rewrite (control-quality repair on a maintainer-ratified split gate) which produces NO verdict (the knull ABLATION itself is unrun). The genuinely verdict-moving items (g2, human f2b-transfer Stage-1, the knull ablation, human g9) are all UNRUN and human/input-blocked, not in flight. Because both per-thesis verdicts are already INCONCLUSIVE-PENDING, no pending item can REVERSE a FEASIBLE/NOT-FEASIBLE call (there is none to reverse): each verdict-moving item RESOLVES the pending INCONCLUSIVE, each refine-only item narrows an envelope.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/feasibility-synthesis.md section 3; registry/experiments/{g3-llmproxy-v3,knull,g2,g3,f2b-transfer,a-f0-mint-economics}.json; docs/next/knull-plain-arm-quality.md sections 3 and 7; tools/registry/audit-status.py ledger", "rationale": "The task authorised authoring the definitive standing verdict unless an in-flight item is load-bearing enough to require waiting; neither in-flight item is (one is a non-discharging weak proxy, the other is a pre-run control repair), so waiting would add latency without changing the standing call.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "resolution_path": "Supersede on read-out of any verdict-moving PENDING item in section 3; g3-llmproxy-v3 and the knull rewrite, when they land, are logged as refinements/preconditions and do not by themselves move the standing verdict."}
197:{"id": "ASM-0762", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Cross-thesis reachability-wall-on-coverage-wall reading (interpretive colour for the capstone; NEVER a premise, load-bearing for nothing; extends ASM-0721 to the efficiency thesis). The programme's measured evidence across BOTH theses is consistent with one shape: the kernel's deterministic machinery is exact and sound INSIDE its own closed grammar / self-authored substrate (l3a/a5 gold-replication identical 527/527 and 855/855; g8 F/B round-trip 33/33; engine exactness 100% on gold), while there is a COVERAGE wall (does the kernel contain the target: g8 0/1000 random Mathlib, m0b 0.3542 friendliest corpus, compression-census ~0.6% roll-up engagement, b-cov-define-lane 0/1550 external items) and, stacked on it, a REACHABILITY wall (even for content the kernel DOES contain and CAN decide perfectly under gold parse, natural language cannot reliably ADDRESS it through the pinned a1-hybrid front-end: l3a-parse 47.6%, a5-nl 41.6%). The one audited efficiency positive (f2b +0.1507) lives strictly inside the fortress (formal, self-authored, alignment-specific), and the neighbouring PASS (truthstyle-2x2) is instrument-adequacy not kernel content. Each constituent figure is index-bound to its own verdict's envelope; the conjunction is direction-only and is confirmed or broken only by the pre-registered per-boundary successors.", "backing_ref": "registry/assessments/{l3a-parse,a5-nl,g8,oracle-coverage,compression-census,b-cov-define-lane,a-e2-census,f2b-replicate,truthstyle-2x2}.json; registry/verdicts/{l3a-parse,a5-nl,g8,m0b,f2b-replicate,truthstyle-2x2}.json; ASM-0721", "rationale": "The pattern is the most consistent thing the registry shows and is worth stating for the maintainer, but it aggregates figures across incommensurable envelopes, so it must remain EXTRAPOLATION and may never premise any verdict.", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "resolution_path": "Each